instruction:
Add 3 missing route imports and registrations to app.ts. Add these imports after the existing route imports (after line 16 'import internalRoutes'):

import injectionRoutes from './routes/injection.js';
import weightRoutes from './routes/weight.js';
import alertRoutes from './routes/alert.js';

Then add these registrations after 'app.register(internalRoutes);' (after line 62):

app.register(injectionRoutes);
app.register(weightRoutes);
app.register(alertRoutes);

Do NOT remove or change any existing code. Only add the 3 imports and 3 register calls. Output the complete modified file.

Add API functions for injection, weight, and alert endpoints to the existing api.ts file. Use the same wrappedFetch pattern and parseJsonOrThrow helper that already exists in this file. Add these functions at the end of the file (before the last closing bracket if any), do NOT remove existing code:

1. Injection API:
- createInjection(payload: {drug: string, doseUnit: number, site: string, injectedAt: string, memo?: string}): POST /api/injection
- fetchInjections(range?: string): GET /api/injections?range={range||'30d'}
- updateInjection(id: string, payload: Partial<{drug: string, doseUnit: number, site: string, injectedAt: string, memo?: string}>): PATCH /api/injection/{id}
- deleteInjection(id: string): DELETE /api/injection/{id}

2. Weight API:
- createWeight(payload: {weightKg: number, memo?: string, measuredAt?: string}): POST /api/weight
- fetchWeights(range?: string): GET /api/weights?range={range||'30d'}
- deleteWeight(id: string): DELETE /api/weight/{id}

3. Alert API:
- fetchAlerts(): GET /api/alerts

All functions should use wrappedFetch and parseJsonOrThrow. Use the same async/export pattern as existing functions like createMealLog, fetchMealLogs etc. Output the COMPLETE file with all existing code preserved plus the new functions added at the end.

Create TypeScript type definitions for the injection feature. Define and export these interfaces:

export interface InjectionInput {
  drug: string;
  doseUnit: number;
  site: 'abdomen' | 'thigh' | 'arm';
  injectedAt: string;
  memo?: string | null;
}

export interface InjectionLog {
  id: string;
  userId: string;
  drug: string;
  doseUnit: number;
  site: 'abdomen' | 'thigh' | 'arm';
  injectedAt: string;
  memo: string | null;
  createdAt: string;
}

export interface InjectionListResponse {
  success: boolean;
  data: InjectionLog[];
}

Output the complete file.

Create TypeScript type definitions for the weight feature. Define and export:

export interface WeightInput {
  weightKg: number;
  memo?: string | null;
  measuredAt?: string;
}

export interface WeightLog {
  id: string;
  userId: string;
  weightKg: number;
  memo: string | null;
  measuredAt: string;
  createdAt: string;
}

export interface WeightListResponse {
  success: boolean;
  data: {
    logs: WeightLog[];
    changeFromFirst: number | null;
    changeFromPrevious: number | null;
    progressToGoal: number | null;
  };
}

Output the complete file.

Create TypeScript type definitions for the alert feature. Define and export:

export interface Alert {
  type: 'muscle_loss' | 'overeating' | 'dehydration' | 'nudge';
  severity: 'warning' | 'info';
  title: string;
  message: string;
  emoji: string;
}

export interface AlertsResponse {
  success: boolean;
  data: Alert[];
}

Output the complete file.
